#eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The remains of a South African National Defence Force Soldier who died in Goma in the DRC have landed back home. Sergeant Vusi Mabena was killed when his helicopter came under fire. READ: SANDF soldier killed in DRC Another crew member suffered injuries but managed to fly the chopper and land safely at Goma Airport. Defence Minister Thandi Modise says it is a sad moment, however, they are proud of the fallen soldier.